Awesome cooking game where it actually goes beyond tapping on the screen a bunch to "cook." The UX feels unusual at first but it works very well and I am impressed at the creativity for making so many functions fit on a small screen. This is definitely worth paying for considering you never get interrupted by annoying ads, and in game purchases are 100% optional unlike some games where you just can't progress without $5 every day. For a buck or two with this app, you can have hours of fun.
